They can afford their singularity", now it is difficult for me to resist an argument.
"Funny.
But not true.
I can prove it to you, right here." he smiled.
His smile seemed familiar.
"Ok smarty pants, I can handle an argument, especially when it has anything to do with my favorite subject - how my life is so peculiarly ordinary", I thought to myself, getting ready for a verbal combat.
"Hey, no need to warm up.
Look, lets scope out a population first, the passengers in this section of the plane.
Each one has their own unique story." he explained gesturing towards the dormant public around.
"No they don't.
Do you see that big group of young people?
Well, what do you think they are doing in this plane?
They are on their way to one of the universities in the US, for their Masters.
