I retaliated rather excitedly.
"Strike one."
I thought.
"Well, they maybe headed to the same country for the same reason, but each one has a different destiny.
The causes behind each one's presence in this plane are different."
he counter argued, but in an irritatingly mild manner.
"Oh really?
You mean finding a well paying job despite the ridiculous conditions that exist in today's markets?
Well, that's not exactly unique you know."
I said a little wary that the discussion could get dirty if this fellow turned out to be a hard core patriot.
"I will show you something.
Look at that guy there.
Everyone at home thinks he is headed for an MS because his parents told him to, so he could get a good job and settle down, probably emigrate.
But you know what?
He really wants to use that education to help in research in his home country.
Find funds to help sponsor research efforts in his field, in his home country.
That girl there.
Back home they think she will get an MS and find an NRI husband.
The best way to settle down quickly in these troubled times.
But the truth is, she wants to be a professor.
A Masters degree in her favorite field will give her the bolstering she needs to become one.
The guy with the funny hair next to her.
His parents want him to get an MBA in an American university so that he has prospects at a global level.
But in reality, he wants to join his father's business and use his education there…", the guy went on telling me a story behind every person I had pointed out saying they were heading to the same place for the same reason.
Each story was unique.
I was tongue tied for some time as I listened to him.
"You know, it is true that at a superficial level, everyone seems to be headed towards the same destination.
However, if you look a little carefully you will realize that each person has a different destiny.
The apparent and the real purposes of our actions are loosely defined.
It is our responsibility to find out which purpose we want to follow.
It may not be always noble, really depends on the person, but it is always closely tied to their passion.", he smiled the familiar smile and lay back on his seat closing his eyes, marking the end of our argument.
As if he knew he had won the argument.
"Maybe he was right.
Maybe each person is not extra ordinary, they really are extraordinary.",
I sighed and looked outside the window, the plane was hovering somewhere above the airport.
"Maybe, or maybe I was talking to myself again..."
