I was not at all inclined on writing an emotional article depicting the sad after effects of leaving home and coming to the other side of the world.
However, an event today, something really amazing has prompted me to pen down the experience which I must say made me realize that Yes!
I am in a different world.
This isn't going to be emotional as I said earlier but well, it has kind of shaken me up from my reverie which was more of a state of denial.
This morning when I started my TO-DO list, I noted a task which said write a post "Home away from home".
It meant nothing then and I wasn't even sure what I was going to put down in that post.
Since most of my stay has been all about dealing with settling down issues, my mind was blank and only had this title drafted in there.
In fact, I smirked at myself thinking what a silly title it seemed.
Little did I know, I was soon going to understand that this was the most appropriate title for my post.
The auditorium was filled with international students.
As the statistics showed there were 70% or more asians.
The presentation went on and then on a particular slide, the presenter had jotted down a point which said "Home away from home".
I pinched myself not really believing this conincidence.
She didn't explain anything about that bullet and so I almost believed it was my imagination.
Of course it wasn't.
